item.title: My Server Development
item.dc:creator: @Gh0st_Jr Gh0st Jr
item.description:
@Gh0st_Jr wrote:

[quote=“primadude, post:8, topic:267083”][quote author=jc22493 link=topic=352624.msg2704624#msg2704624 date=1236889304]

LEECH.

This is my old server; Summon-Pkz.
I’ll even post the code that opens the Lost City quest interface with because I still have my old server.

[code]case 28166:
switch (q1) {
case 0:
c.loadquest(“Lost City”, “Requirements for this Quest:”, “”, “Level 36 Woodcutting”,
“Level 31 Fletching”, “Ability to defeat a level 101 Enemy with no weapon or armour.”, “”, “I can start this quest by speaking to the”,
“Adventurers Near the Lumbridge swamp.”, “”);
break;

	case 1:
		c.loadquest("Lost City", "", "The Warrior told me to get Him Four sharks,", "and a Steel Battleaxe, in Exchange for,",
			"Information on Zanaris.", "", "", "I should speak to the Warrior once I",
			"Have collected these items for him.", "");	
		break;
	case 2:
		c.loadquest("Lost City", "", "The Warrior told me I can obtain A Dramen staff from Entrana.", "I will need to go To the north west of Entrana,",
			"to the Entrance of the Dungeon, and Defeat the", "Level 101 tree spirit, with no Weapons or armour.", "", "Once I have done this, I have to go back to",
			"the Warrior, for Information on the Whereabouts of Zanaris.", "");	
		break;
	case 3:
		c.loadquest("Lost City", "", "I have defeated the Tree Spirit guarding the Dramen Tree.", "I now need to cut a Dramen branch from the tree,",
			"and fletch it into a Dramen staff.", "", "", "Once I have done this, I Should see the Warrior again",
			"for him to tell me Where the Entrance to Zanaris is.", "");	
		break;
	case 4:
		c.loadquest("Lost City", "", "The warrior has told me the Entrance to Zanaris is", "in the middle of Lumbridge Swamp.",
			"", "I must now find it and Enter Zanaris, to", "finish this quest.", "",
			"", "");	
		break;
	case 5:
		c.loadquest("Lost City", "", "", "QUEST COMPLETED",
			"", "The reward to this quest was the ability to Purchase", "and wield the Dragon dagger and LongSword.", "",
			"", "");
		break;
}
break;[/code]

That was in Buttons.java.

He just got owned.
[/quote]

I hate people who blatantly leech when they know It’s not theirs.[/quote]

  • Prima —
    ummm didnt u release it? and he might have kept some things on it?

Read full topic
